<dl id="n11015a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11015a">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11015a"> 15(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Again! / <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">They lay on earth,</span></span> <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">under sheltered</span></span> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">enfolded</span></span><font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">by / the night</span></span> / <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">They lay on earth,</span></span> <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">nightfolded,</span></span> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">folded by night</span></span><font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">and I heard</span></span> / <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">Her word</span></span> / <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>Together<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> Folded by <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>the<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> night they lay on earth <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">&amp;</span></span> I hear<span class="strike"><span class="striketext">d</span></span> / From far her low word breathed on <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">my</span></span> / <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">me,</span></span> on my fading brain / <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">And I come to you.</span></span> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">Come</span></span><font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">Bend deep upon / me. I am here.</span></span> / Come! <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">Take me</span></span> I yield<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font>! <span class="strike"><span class="striketext">I yield.</span></span> Bend deep upon / me. I am here! / Subduer of pride, my only love, my anguish, / Take me, save me, soothe me, O spare me! </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Written sideways on page. Draft of third stanza of Joyce&apos;s poem, &lsquo;A Prayer&rsquo; (published in 1927 in <i>Pomes Penyeach</i>: <br>Again! Together, folded by the night, they lay on earth. I hear <br>From far her low word breathe on my breaking brain. <br>Come! I yield. Bend deeper upon me! I am here. <br>Subduer, do not leave me! Only joy, only anguish, <br>Take me, save me, soothe me, O spare me!). <br>See notecooks pages 11 and 13 for the first and second stanzas. The TS of the poem is dated 18 May 1924.</mm> </dd></dl>
